            . On the 8th of June I saw the prisoner at the door of a gunmaker's shop in Little Ayliff-street; I asked him if he had got a pistol for sale? he said he had, and produced it. I asked him where he got it from? he hesitated, and said he had it from a gentleman's servant at Clapton, that the gentleman had been in the cavalry, and had given it to him. I went to Mr. Sparks, and his gardener claimed it.</p>
